BRAT_GEOMETRY: The BRAT drainage network: NHD Flowlines that have been segmented to 300 m.
BRAT: The output network of the BRAT tool, with various attributes added representing model intermediates and outputs.
EXVEG_SUIT: The existing vegetation raster classified into suitability for dam building material, where 0 is unsuitable and 4 is preferred.
HISTVEG_SUIT: The historice vegetation raster classified into suitability for dam building material, where 0 is unsuitable and 4 is preferred.
DGO_GEOM: Discrete Geographic Objects - The valley bottom split into a sampling frame of polygons where the IGO points are at the center of each polygon.
BRAT_DGOS: DGOs attributed with values related to BRAT outputs calculated within the DGO extent.
IGO_GEOM: Integrated Geographic Objects - Points placed at a specified distance interval along the valley centerline. This distance is a function of the average valley width for a given stream.
BRAT_IGOS: IGOs attributed with values related to BRAT outputs calculated within a single DGO or an aggregation of DGOs.
